Tensor Module - Aggregation of Tensor Field Infrastructure

This module re-exports all tensor-related submodules, providing a single import point for the full tensor field stack:

  • globaltensor â€” TensorField[D,R,L,T]: distributed fields with ghost regions, GlobalShifter transport, and discrete Laplacian
  • localtensor â€” LocalTensorField[D,R,L,T]: rank-local host-memory views of global fields
  • tensorview â€” TensorFieldView[L,T]: device-side views for the each macro (OpenCL / SYCL / OpenMP)
  • stencil â€” LatticeStencil[D]: unified stencil operations across all backends

Data flows through the stack as:

TensorField  â†’  LocalTensorField  â†’  TensorFieldView  â†’  Kernels
  (GA/MPI)          (host RAM)          (device buffers)    (each macro)

For distributed-memory shifting and stencil operations that do not require device dispatch, use GlobalShifter and discreteLaplacian from globaltensor directly.

Imports

globaltensor, localtensor, tensorview, ../lattice/stencil
